OL,3,CMan accused of posting offensive
OL,4,Cmaterial online has case dropped
OL,6,FIn an address to Judge Nicholas
OL,7,FBarker, prosecutor Tim Evans said the
OL,8,Fprosecution had, following a review of
OL,9,Fthe case, taken the view that it was
OL,10,Fnot in the public interest to proceed.
OL,11,FAs a result, the case against Mr
OL,12,FGlaister was being discontinued.
OL,14,FThat decision was formally conveyed to
OL,15,FMr Glaister by Judge Barker, who
OL,16,Fconcluded it had been "quite proper"
OL,17,Ffor police to have taken action in the
OL,18,Fcounty early last month during a
OL,19,F"period of great sensitivity".
