OL,3,CMan accused of posting offensive
OL,4,Cmaterial online has case dropped
OL,6,FThe court heard he had shared
OL,7,Foffensive material, but had not
OL,8,Fwritten it himself.
OL,10,FIt had not been "necessary", said the
OL,11,Fjudge, for the prosecution to proceed
OL,12,Fwith the case, meaning that Mr
OL,13,FGlaister faces no further action.
OL,15,F"You are now very much on the police's
OL,16,Fradar," said Judge Barker as he issued
OL,17,Fadvice about any online use going
OL,18,Fforward.
